+## Rules — DO NOT VIOLATE
+
+1. **Sponsor firewall.** Everything this stage produces — notes, relationships, segments, spend/attendance/no-show history, list membership — is operator-internal. None of it may enter `sponsor_audience_member`, the `lib/intelligence/sponsor-safe.ts` types, sponsor briefings, or external share surfaces. `tests/unit/sponsor-firewall.test.ts` is the gate.
+2. **Segments and statuses always map to display names** — raw keys (`big_spender`, `no_show_risk`, `WAITLISTED`) never reach the UI.
+3. **Attendance truth is check-in** (`RSVP.checkedIn`); spend truth is **captured** payments. Don't re-derive these anywhere else — `lib/member-history.ts` is the single tested definition.
+4. The Remember + connections engines stay **pure** (no I/O); callers fetch rows.
+5. **No influence score; reach never ranks.** The falsification run (120 members / 6 events, `lib/member-connections.ts` header) showed co-attendance reach is ~0.85 correlated with raw attendance and caught 0/8 seeded connectors; gravity (brought/referred who stuck, in captured dollars) caught 8/8. Don't collapse primitives into a score, don't rank by centrality, and don't ship aggregate ratio/segment rollups as ranking signals. Relationship claims in UI use provable verbs only — "met" is never asserted.
+6. Email is the load-bearing identity key (`@@unique([workspaceId, email])`) — quick-add must not make it nullable (synthetic-email convention instead; Q-Capture).
