+# UI Spec — The Gravity Ledger ("Who's driving your room — and your revenue")
+
+_Design + copy spec only. No code. Author: design session 2026-06-09. Status: **FINAL — Adam's decisions folded 2026-06-09; ready for build.** §12 records the explicit decisions and the standing defaults._
+
+The operator surface that answers one question with receipts: **who pulls people into your room, do those people stick, and what have they spent.** Every row is a person; every person ends in an action — Comp Access, an Event Access invite, or a win-back. There is no aggregate layer, no composition chart, no score. The number that ranks the page is captured dollars.
+
+## 1. Why this shape — the falsification result (design law for this surface)
+
+The falsification run (120 members / 6 events, documented in the `lib/member-connections.ts` header, `member-connections` worktree, commit `6ee4d30`):
+
+- **Co-attendance "reach" is ~0.85 correlated with raw attendance** and flattens at club scale — everyone overlaps with everyone. It re-states "who comes a lot."
+- **Reach caught 0 of 8 seeded low-attendance connectors.** The people who actually built the room were invisible to a centrality ranking.
+- **Gravity — brought/referred edges where the person STUCK — caught 8/8.**
+
+Consequences, binding on this design:
+
+1. **No rollup layer.** No returning-vs-new ratio, no segment chips, no "your room at a glance" header stats. That layer is attendance-frequency theater.
+2. **No influence score.** The engine deliberately exposes primitives and refuses to collapse them; the UI honors that. Rank = captured dollars driven, ties broken by stuck count. A number with a unit, never an index.
+3. **Reach/centrality never ranks anyone on this surface.** `distinctCoAttendees` does not appear.
+4. **Every element ends in an operator action.** If a fact doesn't change what the operator does next, it doesn't render.
+
+## 2. Where it lives
+
+- **Surface:** evolves the existing **Connectors** page in place — `/operator/members/connectors` (today: Layer 1, referral counts only, no dollars, no actions). Same URL, same nav links from the Members area (per `UX-MEMBERS-CRM.md` IA). Renaming is §12.2.
+- **Page title:** `Connectors` (PP Editorial New italic — the one display-serif element, per `UI-MEMBERS-CRM.md`: display for the page title only, never for data).
+- **Subtitle:** **"Who's driving your room — and your revenue."**
+- **Access:** page is READ_ONLY+ (as today, `requireRolePage`). Action buttons render for STAFF+ only; the server-side `requireRole` on each write path remains the real boundary.
+- **Never sponsor-facing — §11.**
+
+## 3. Data contract (engine truth — `lib/member-connections.ts`)
+
+| Primitive | Provable as | Never phrased as |
+|---|---|---|
+| **Brought** | an RSVP whose `plusOneOfMemberId` points at them | "knows," "came with" (beyond the literal plus-one fact) |
+| **Referred** | a `Member.referredByMemberId` edge | "vouched for," "close to" |
+| **Stuck** | the brought/referred person has **≥ 2 check-ins of their own** (`STUCK_MIN_EVENTS`) | "loyal," "converted fan" |
+| **Gravity in dollars** | sum of **CAPTURED** spend (`paymentStatus === 'CAPTURED'`) of the people they brought + referred | "GMV," "LTV," projections of any kind |
+| **Lapsed** | ≥ 120 days since their own last check-in (`DEFAULT_SEGMENT_THRESHOLDS.lapsedAfterDays`, shared with `lib/member-history.ts`) | "lost," "churned" |
+
+**The "met" law:** co-presence is not acquaintance. "Met," "knows," "friends," "connected with" are **banned strings** on this surface. The only relationship verbs allowed are the provable ones: *brought*, *referred*, *checked in*. (Check-in-gap proximity — "checked in 7 minutes apart" — is a provable fact the engine exposes; whether it's allowed as secondary receipt color is §12.5. It never ranks.)
+
+Composition note: this surface joins two pure engines — `member-connections` (edges, gravity) and `member-history` (own attendance, lapse). A workspace-wide roll (derive per member over the same row set) is implementation work the engines already support.
+
+## 4. Structure — three action queues, nothing else
+
+"Faces to know" is no longer a sub-section; it is the entire surface. Three queues, each a list of person-rows, each row ending in exactly one primary action. A person appears in **one queue only** (first match in the order below). No queue header shows a count larger than its list — no totals, no header stats.
+
+**The gravity bar (decided 2026-06-09):** a person appears on this surface with **≥1 stuck edge — the primary gate** — or, failing that, **≥ $500 driven**. Dollars alone admit someone whose people spent but haven't stuck yet; a stuck edge admits someone even in an all-free program.
+
+| Queue | Eyebrow | Membership (provable conditions) | Primary action |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| 1 | **EARNED A COMP** | clears the gravity bar **and** active (own check-in within 120 days) **and** not comped in the last 90 days (re-comp guard — decided, §12.8) | **Comp Access** |
+| 2 | **WORTH WINNING BACK** | clears the gravity bar **and** lapsed (own last check-in ≥ 120 days ago) | **Win back** (invite + optional House Phone text) |
+| 3 | **GET THEM IN THE ROOM** | clears the gravity bar **and** not confirmed for the soonest published upcoming event | **Invite** (Event Access) |
+
+Within each queue: sort by dollars driven desc, then stuck count desc. Queue caps at 8 rows with a quiet "Show all N →" expander — a cap is honesty about attention, and the expander means nothing is silently dropped.
+
+If the workspace has **zero captured revenue overall** (all-free programming), the dollar figures are hidden everywhere and stuck counts lead — showing "$0" down a whole column would be its own kind of theater (§12.7).
+
+## 5. Row anatomy — person, dollars, evidence, action
+
+```
+┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
+│ EARNED A COMP                                                    │
+│                                                                  │
+│ ◉ Marcus King                                  $1,840 captured   │
+│   Brought 3 as plus-ones; 2 now come on their own.               │
+│   ▸ Receipts                      [Comp Access]  View record →   │
+│                                                                  │
+│ ◉ Aria Chen                                      $980 captured   │
+│   Referred 2; both stuck.                                        │
+│   ▸ Receipts                      [Comp Access]  View record →   │
+└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
+```
+
+Per row, top to bottom:
+
+1. **Identity** — avatar + full name (operator surface; links to `/operator/members/[id]`).
+2. **The number** — right-aligned, `text-text-primary`, tabular numerals: **"$1,840 captured"**. Always labeled with its unit and provenance word ("captured"); never a bare number, never "GMV" (jargon — internal docs may say gravity/GMV; UI says captured).
+3. **The evidence line** — one sentence, `text-text-secondary`, provable verbs only:
+   - "Brought 3 as plus-ones; 2 now come on their own."
+   - "Referred 2; both stuck — 7 check-ins between them."
+   - Win-back variant carries the tension: "Referred 2 who still come. She hasn't checked in since Feb 2 — 127 days."
+   - Invite variant carries the gap: "Brought 2 who stuck. Not on the list for Summer Solstice."
+4. **Receipts** (collapsed disclosure, "▸ Receipts") — the full provable chain, one line per edge:
+   - "Maya Reyes — plus-one at Backyard Vol. 2 · 4 check-ins since · $920 captured"
+   - "Jordan Tate — referred · 3 check-ins · $740 captured"
+   - "Priya Shah — plus-one at Solstice · 1 check-in · $180 captured" *(not yet stuck — shown honestly, never hidden)*
+   - Every receipt name links to that member's record. Edge type + origin event + their own subsequent behavior + their captured spend. Nothing inferred.
+5. **Actions** — one primary button (NBC Red, per the all-buttons law) + quiet text links:
+   - Queue 1: **[Comp Access]** → the existing comp flow, event picker defaulting to the soonest published upcoming event. `aria-label="Comp Access for Marcus King"`.
+   - Queue 2: **[Invite back]** → Event Access invite (operator-origin, existing write path); secondary text link **"Text via House Phone"** when `member.phone` exists and House Phone is configured (House Phone send path only — no new Twilio surface).
+   - Queue 3: **[Invite to {event}]** → Event Access invite with event picker, soonest first.
+   - All rows: **"View record →"** quiet link.
+   - READ_ONLY sees the row without buttons (links remain); hiding is UX only, `requireRole(STAFF)` on the routes is the boundary.
+
+**Stuck-related wording:** never reuse "regular" (that's the 3+-attended history segment — different threshold, different meaning). The stuck phrase is "come(s) on their own" with the receipt showing the literal check-in count.
+
+## 6. Copy — exact strings per state
+
+Voice: a ledger kept by a host — warm but auditable. Every sentence must survive the question "can the database prove this?" Sentence case, numerals, captured dollars only, no exclamation marks. "Event Access" / "Comp Access" — never "RSVP."
+
+### 6.1 Populated (the normal state)
+
+- Title: **"Connectors"** · Subtitle: **"Who's driving your room — and your revenue."**
+- Queue eyebrows as in §4. Each eyebrow gets one sub-line, `text-text-muted`:
+  - EARNED A COMP — **"Their pull filled seats. Reward it."**
+  - WORTH WINNING BACK — **"Their people still come. They've stopped."**
+  - GET THEM IN THE ROOM — **"Proven pull, no spot reserved yet."**
+- Evidence + receipts grammar per §5.
+
+### 6.2 Sparse (edges exist; nobody stuck, nothing captured)
+
+Queues that would be empty are hidden (never an empty box with a header). In their place, one block:
+
+- **"Pull is forming."**
+- **"4 plus-one edges and 2 referrals are on the books, but no one has hit 2 check-ins of their own yet — that's the bar for 'stuck.' Nothing to act on until they do."**
+- Below it, the edge list renders as plain receipts (provable, but no actions — there is no honest action to attach yet).
+
+### 6.3 Empty (no provable edges at all)
+
+- **"No provable pull yet."**
+- **"This ledger builds itself from Event Access: plus-ones create brought edges when they check in, and referrals create referred edges. Set a referrer on a member record to start the graph."**
+- One primary button: **[Open Members]** → `/operator/members`. (Even the empty state ends in an action.)
+
+### 6.4 Loading
+
+Skeleton: three eyebrow-width bars, each over 2–3 row skeletons (avatar circle + two line bars + button-width pill). Fixed min-height; no spinner. No micro-caption — this page's tone is ledger, not lyric.
+
+### 6.5 Error
+
+- **"Couldn't load the ledger."**
+- **"The rest of the Members area is unaffected. Try again."** — "Try again" is a quiet text link that refetches (an error retry is not promoted to a red CTA).
+- Implementation note (binding): the catch **must log** with workspace id context. Action buttons never render against stale/partial data — a half-loaded ledger that lets you comp someone is worse than an error.
+
+### 6.6 Post-action feedback
+
+Inline on the row, replacing the primary button: **"Comped for Summer Solstice ✓"** / **"Invited to Summer Solstice ✓"** / **"Text sent ✓"** — `text-text-secondary`, with an "Undo"-equivalent only where the underlying write path supports it (comp/invite have cancel paths; SMS does not — no fake undo). The row stays in place until reload; queues don't reshuffle mid-glance.
+
+## 7. What is deliberately NOT on this page
+
+- Returning/new ratios, segment chips, proportion bars (falsified — §1).
+- `distinctCoAttendees` / reach / any centrality figure.
+- A workspace "total driven" headline stat — a total you can't act on is a vanity number.
+- An influence score or rank index of any kind.
+- "Met at," "knows," "friend of" — non-provable social claims.
+- Charisma / vibe / "die-hard energy" — per the engine header, that lives in operator notes and tags, not transactional data; it does not rank this page.
+
+## 8. Visual language (semantic tokens only — no hex)
+
+- Page chrome matches the Members area (`UI-MEMBERS-CRM.md`): wide gutters, `PageHeader` with crumbs `Members / Connectors`.
+- Eyebrows: `text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-text-muted`.
+- Rows: list (not DataTable — evidence sentences need a reading line, not cells), separated by `border-border` hairlines on `bg-surface`. Dollar figures in tabular numerals, `text-text-primary`.
+- Evidence `text-sm text-text-secondary`; receipts `text-sm` with `text-text-muted` separators (·).
+- Primary action buttons: NBC Red (`bg-primary`), one per row. Win-back's "Text via House Phone" and "View record →" are quiet text links.
+- Disclosure (▸ Receipts) uses the Radix disclosure primitive; chevron + label, not icon-only.
+- No warning/alarm tones anywhere — this page has no risk layer; lapse is framed as opportunity (win back), not infraction.
+- Day/night via tokens only.
+
+## 9. Accessibility
+
+- Each queue is a `region` with its eyebrow as the accessible name; rows are list items.
+- Buttons carry person + event context in `aria-label` ("Invite Dana Whitfield to Summer Solstice").
+- Receipts disclosure is keyboard-operable with state announced (expanded/collapsed).
+- Dollar figures are text, not color-coded; meaning never rides on color alone. AA contrast via tokens.
+
+## 10. Terminology audit
+
+- "Event Access" / "Comp Access" canonical; **"RSVP" appears nowhere** (the brought edge is described as "plus-one," its UI-lawful name).
+- No raw enums (`CAPTURED` → "captured"; statuses always mapped).
+- "Guest" reserved for its access-group meaning; this page says "members" / "people" / names.
+- "Stuck" is internal vocabulary — UI renders it as "come on their own" + literal counts (§12.3 decides whether "stuck" may appear verbatim).
+
+## 11. Sponsor firewall — hard rules
+
+This page concentrates the three most radioactive data classes in the product: **who brought whom** (relationship edges), **per-person captured spend**, and **operator intent** (who we plan to comp). All operator-internal, with the same teeth as `UI-REMEMBER-CARD.md` §10:
+
+1. Operator-authed surface and API only; renders nothing without a resolved workspace + role.
+2. **Never** enters `sponsor_audience_member`, the `lib/intelligence/sponsor-safe.ts` types, sponsor briefings, or AI-composed sponsor narratives. Relationship edges are explicitly named in the roadmap firewall: sponsors never learn who vouched for or brought whom.
+3. **Never** on external share surfaces or any tokened public page.
+4. Comp/invite/win-back queue membership is operator intent — it must not leak through notifications, exports, or webhook payloads that reach sponsors.
+5. `tests/unit/sponsor-firewall.test.ts` stays the gate; no sponsor-safe type may widen to carry edges, spend, or queue membership.
+
+## 12. Decisions (Adam, 2026-06-09) + standing defaults
+
+Items 1, 6, 8, 9 were decided explicitly; the rest were specced defaults Adam let stand by marking this spec final. Build to all of them.
+
+1. **Queue thresholds — DECIDED.** Gravity bar: **≥1 stuck edge (primary gate)** OR ≥ $500 driven. Active/lapsed boundary stays 120 days (shared with `member-history`). Folded into §4.
+2. **Page identity — default stands.** Evolve "Connectors" in place; URL and nav unchanged; subtitle carries the new claim.
+3. **"Gravity"/"stuck" as UI words — default stands.** Both stay internal; UI says "driving" / "come on their own."
+4. **Win-back composition — default stands.** Invite + House Phone text link when `member.phone` exists and Twilio is configured; Twilio stays House Phone-only.
+5. **Check-in-gap color — default stands.** Proximity is excluded entirely; it never appears as receipt detail.
+6. **Retrofit the pre-event card — DECIDED.** Cut the ratio bar, the segment chips, and any score from `UI-REMEMBER-CARD.md`; keep **exactly one descriptive (non-ranking) composition line**. That spec was amended same-day to match — see its §3.
+7. **Zero-revenue degradation — default stands.** A workspace with no captured revenue hides the $ figures and leads with stuck counts (§4).
+8. **Re-comp guard — DECIDED, approved at 90 days.** EARNED A COMP excludes anyone comped in the last 90 days ("last comped" lookback via RSVP `isComp` + audit trail). Folded into §4.
+9. **Doc drift — DECIDED: logged, not fixed.** The phantom `INFLUENCE-MODEL.md` citation in `connectors/page.tsx` is recorded as a one-line cleanup item in this stage's `CONTEXT.md`; do not fix out-of-band.
+
+## 13. Out of scope
+
+- The pre-event audience summary card (`UI-REMEMBER-CARD.md`) and the member-record "sphere of influence" card — siblings, not this surface.
+- Engine changes (`lib/member-connections.ts`, `lib/member-history.ts` stay pure; `STUCK_MIN_EVENTS` and thresholds are code constants here).
+- The workspace-wide derivation wrapper, caching, and API route (implementation).
+- Any new relationship types (brought/referred only — `MemberRelationship` typed edges are roadmap §4.2, a separate decision).
