+# Members CRM — Visual System Spec (Form)
+
+_Author: Form (visual). Application surface, not a marketing page: the form-web conversion vocabulary (Hook/CTA/social proof) does not apply; this is a designed system for an operator tool. Tokens only, no hex. 7-theme white-label safe (every value is a token that themes override). Handoff target: Prism. Grounded in `app/globals.css` + `app/operator/members/`._
+
+---
+
+## 1. Foundations (state once, every surface inherits)
+
+### Type
+- **Display** — PP Editorial New, regular italic. Use for the one page title per surface only (member name, "Members", "Connectors"). Never for data.
+- **UI / body** — Neue Haas Grotesk Display Pro. Everything else.
+
+Semantic type scale (replace ad-hoc `text-[10px]`/`text-[11px]` drift with named roles, max 3 per section):
+
+| Role | Size / line | Weight | Token use | Where |
+|------|-------------|--------|-----------|-------|
+| `display` | 28-32 / 1.1 | 400 italic | PP Editorial | page title (name, surface title) |
+| `title` | 18-20 / 1.3 | 600 | text-text-primary | card-less section title |
+| `body` | 14 / 1.5 | 400 | text-text-primary | record values, table cells |
+| `meta` | 13 / 1.4 | 400 | text-text-secondary | secondary line, email, descriptor |
+| `label` | 11 / 1.2, tracking 0.14em, uppercase | 600 | text-text-muted | card labels, column headers |
+| `micro` | 10 / 1.2, tracking 0.12em, uppercase | 600 | text-text-muted | badges, counts |
+
+Rule: kill the `text-[8px]`/`text-[9px]` one-offs. Sort indicators and the like use `micro`.
+
+### Spacing
+8px base. Stops: 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 48. Card padding `20` (p-5). Card-to-card gap `20` (space-y-5). Intra-card section gap `16`. Row vertical rhythm `12`. No values off-scale.
+
+### Color (tokens, theme-driven)
+| Role | Token |
+|------|-------|
+| Page background | `--bg` (`bg` util) |
+| Card / surface | `--card`, `--surface`, elevated `--surface-elevated` |
+| Hover wash | `--muted` (`bg-muted`) |
+| Border | `--border`, strong `--border-strong` |
+| Text | `--text-primary` / `secondary` / `muted` |
+| Brand / primary action | `--primary` (NoBC Red base; purple in night themes) + `--primary-soft` |
+| Positive / caution / negative | `--success` / `--warning` / `--danger` + `-soft` |
+| On-primary | `--on-primary` |
+
+The Purple list accent currently hardcodes `#C7A7DE`. **Before/after: replace with `--accent` (or a new `--list-purple` token) so it themes.** This is the one live hex literal in the members surface.
+
+### Radius / elevation / motion
+- Radius: `--radius-base` (cards), `6px` (inputs/cells/chips). Use tokens, not literals.
+- Elevation: `--card-shadow` resting, `--card-shadow-hover` on interactive cards only. Flat by default; shadow signals "you can act on this."
+- Motion: functional only. 120-160ms ease on hover wash, cell-edit focus, toast in/out. No decorative animation.
+
+---
+
+## 2. The card + table system
+
+### Card (the aside unit)
+One pattern everywhere: `rounded-[--radius-base] border border-border bg-card p-5`, label in `label` role at top, content below with `16` gap. The current Notes/Assessment/Sphere/Editable cards already converge on this; the spec makes it canonical. Cards do not nest. A card has exactly one `label`.
+
+### Table (the roster)
+- Header row: `label` role, `--border` bottom rule, sortable headers carry the `micro` direction glyph right-aligned for numeric columns.
+- Row: `12` vertical padding, full-row hover wash (`bg-muted`), identity cell is the dominant element (avatar 32 + name `body` 600 + email `meta`).
+- Editable cell: resting shows value or a `meta`-muted placeholder at 60% opacity that lifts to 100% on row hover (the "this is fillable" tell). Editing state: `6px` input, `--primary` border. This pattern already exists in `InlineEditCell`; standardize it across the configurable columns.
+- Density: one comfortable density (`12` row padding). A future compact toggle is out of scope.
+
+---
+
+## 3. Hierarchy per surface
+
+### Roster (dominant element: the identity column)
+Order top to bottom: page title (`display`) + count (`meta`) and actions row → toolbar (search left, facet chips, count right) → table. The toolbar is one band, not three; search and chips share a row at `8` gap. Bulk bar overlays sticky on selection.
+
+### Record (dominant element: the name + descriptor)
+Header: name (`display`) → descriptor (`meta`, "Founder at Stripe · Fintech") → contact (`meta`-muted). Then the status strip (lifecycle + tags + 4-stat rail). Then the 2-col grid: Activity (wide, left) | aside rail (right). Aside order by operator priority: Notes (running read) → Sphere → Assessment → Fields. Once the rail exceeds ~4 cards (reporting lands later), introduce record tabs (Overview / Activity / Relationships / Fields) per RESOLVED-IA-2 pending.
+
+### Connectors (dominant element: rank + name)
+Rank numeral in `--text-tertiary`, connector identity `body`, the two counts right-aligned `body`. Top connector gets no special chrome; the ranking itself is the signal.
+
+---
+
+## 4. Empty + loading states (designed, not blank)
+
+| Surface | Empty | Loading |
+|---------|-------|---------|
+| Roster (no members) | icon + `No members yet` + link `Review applications` | server-rendered, arrives populated |
+| Roster (no match) | centered `meta`: `No members match "{q}".` | n/a (client filter) |
+| Record island (notes/timeline/sphere) | `meta`-muted one-liner ("No notes yet. Leave one for your team.") | `meta`-muted `Loading…`; upgrade to a 2-line skeleton at `--muted` |
+| Connectors | `meta`: `No referrals recorded yet. Set a referrer on a record to start the graph.` | server-rendered |
+
+Skeletons over spinners for the record islands: two muted bars at `--muted`, `12` gap, so the layout never jumps.
+
+---
+
+## 5. Component list for Prism
+
+| Component | Surfaces | Variants | Existing |
+|-----------|----------|----------|----------|
+| PageHeader (title/descriptor/actions) | all | display title, optional descriptor line | yes |
+| DataTable (shell/head/row/cell) | roster, connectors | sortable header, numeric-right, hover | yes |
+| InlineEditCell | roster, record | default/empty/editing/saving/error/readonly | yes (extend to Role, Industry, custom) |
+| Card | record aside | one label, optional count | yes (ad-hoc; standardize) |
+| Facet chip / SortButton | roster | active/idle | yes |
+| Badge (lifecycle / red list / tag / provenance) | record, roster | tones via semantic tokens | yes |
+| Skeleton (2-line) | record islands | n/a | **no — build** |
+| Configurable-column control | roster | menu of firmographic + custom fields | **no — build (per RESOLVED-EDIT-1 full customization)** |
+
+---
+
+## 6. Top before/after fixes (highest visual ROI)
+
+1. ■ Replace the `#C7A7DE` Purple-list hex with a token (`--accent` / `--list-purple`) so it themes. Only live hex in the surface.
+2. ▲ Adopt the named type scale; remove `text-[8/9/12px]` one-offs and the 0.14 vs 0.18 tracking drift between card labels.
+3. ▲ Unify the roster toolbar into one band (search + chips + count), aligned to the table grid.
+4. ▲ Record islands: skeletons instead of `Loading…` text, so the rail never jumps.
+5. ● Standardize the Card pattern (one label, `p-5`, `space-y-5`) and the editable-cell placeholder lift across all configurable columns.
+
+None of this changes data or the firewall. It is hierarchy, scale, and token discipline: the difference between refined defaults and a designed system.
