+# UI Spec — "Remember" Pre-Event Audience Summary Card
+
+_Design + copy spec only. No code. Author: design session 2026-06-09. Status: **draft, amended 2026-06-09** per Adam's decision in `UI-GRAVITY-LEDGER.md` §12.6: the ratio bar, segment chips, and any score are **cut**; exactly one descriptive (non-ranking) composition line remains. Remaining open decisions in §11._
+
+The card that turns `lib/member-history.ts` (Phase C, on the `remember-history` worktree branch) into a single glanceable read of who is coming to an upcoming event. The product moment: **event #2 is not a blank slate** — the operator walks in already knowing who came back, who's brand new, who's worth a word at the door.
+
+---
+
+## 1. Where it lives
+
+- **Surface:** `/operator/events/[id]` → **Overview tab**, main column.
+- **Position:** directly **below the stat-card row** (Confirmed / Capacity Left / Revenue / Days Until), **above "About this event."** Rationale: the stat cards answer *how many*; this card answers *who*. That is the natural reading order for an operator glancing at an upcoming event.
+- **Visibility:** upcoming events only (`isPast === false`). Past events get the event retro (a separate future Remember surface — out of scope here, noted in the engine header).
+- **Audience:** operators only, all roles including READ_ONLY (it is a read surface). **Never sponsor-facing — see §10.**
+
+## 2. Data contract (what the engine gives us)
+
+From `summarizeMemberHistory` + `classifyMember` per confirmed person:
+
+| Field | Meaning (engine truth) |
+|---|---|
+| `timesRegistered` | Confirmed registrations (excludes declined/waitlisted) |
+| `eventsAttended` | Checked in — attendance truth is the door, not the registration |
+| `noShows` | Held a confirmed/comp spot for a past event, never checked in |
+| `totalSpendCents` | Captured revenue only (authorized ≠ revenue; comp = $0) |
+| `lastAttendedAt` / `firstAttendedAt` | Most recent / earliest check-in |
+| Segments | `regular` (3+ attended) · `big_spender` ($500+ captured lifetime) · `no_show_risk` (2+ no-shows) · `lapsed` (120+ days since last attendance) · `first_timer` (≤1 attended, ≥1 registered). Multi-membership allowed; `[]` = no signal. |
+
+**Display-layer definitions this spec adds** (documented divergence, not engine changes):
+
+- **Returning** = `eventsAttended ≥ 1` *prior to this event*. The composition math assumes history rows **exclude** the current event's own registration (open decision §11.3).
+- **First-timer (display)** = `eventsAttended === 0` — literally never been. The engine's `first_timer` (≤1, "a face to convert") is a conversion-targeting net; on this card a stricter definition keeps "18 returning / 14 first-timers" from overlapping and breaking the operator's mental math.
+
+## 3. Information hierarchy
+
+Four levels, strictly ordered. The card is read top-to-bottom in under five seconds.
+
+1. **The read** — one editorial headline sentence. The synthesis, not the numbers. This is what the operator remembers walking to the venue.
+2. **The composition line** — exactly **one** descriptive sentence: how much of the room has been here before. Descriptive, not ranking — it makes no claim about who matters.
+3. **The people** — "Faces to know": up to 3 named lines. The hosting moves.
+4. **Provenance footer** — where this comes from + the path to the full list.
+
+> **Cut by decision (2026-06-09, `UI-GRAVITY-LEDGER.md` §12.6):** the proportion bar, the segment chips (Regulars / Big spenders / Back after a break / First-timers / No-show risk), and any score. The falsification run showed the aggregate rollup is attendance-frequency theater; people ranked by gravity belong on the Gravity Ledger, not here. No-show risk no longer appears anywhere on this card — those names stay findable in the guest list.
+
+## 4. Anatomy
+
+```
+┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
+│ WHO'S COMING                                  (eyebrow) │
+│                                                         │
+│ A familiar room, meeting new faces.    (serif italic)   │
+│ 18 of 32 confirmed have been here       (composition    │
+│ before.                                  line)          │
+│                                                         │
+│ FACES TO KNOW                                           │
+│ Marcus K. — 4th event, back after 4 months.             │
+│ Sofia R. — regular, 8 events, $1,240 lifetime.          │
+│ Dana W. — first event since January.                    │
+│                                                         │
+│ Based on check-ins across your events · See the full    │
+│ list →                                       (footer)   │
+└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
+```
+
+## 5. Visual language (semantic tokens only — no hex, per Absolute Rules)
+
+- **Container:** `rounded-lg border border-border bg-surface-elevated`, generous padding (matches the Run of Show block family on the same tab, slightly roomier).
+- **Eyebrow:** matches the existing section-heading pattern on this tab — `text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-text-muted`.
+- **Headline:** `var(--font-display)` (PP Editorial New), *italic*, ~`text-2xl`, `text-text-primary`. The only serif on the card. Minimum ~20px for italic-serif legibility (AA).
+- **Composition line:** Neue Haas via body stack, `text-base text-text-secondary`, max ~`62ch`. Exactly one sentence — no bar, no chips, no counts beyond it (cut 2026-06-09).
+- **Faces to know:** name in medium weight `text-text-primary`; the story clause `text-text-secondary`. List, not cards.
+- **Footer:** `text-xs text-text-muted`; "See the full list →" is a quiet text link (`text-text-secondary`, underline on hover) — not a button, so the all-buttons-are-NBC-Red law isn't invoked.
+- Day/night: tokens only; nothing on this card hardcodes a mode.
+
+## 6. Copy — every state, exact strings
+
+Voice: a host's brief, not an analytics report. Sentence case. Numerals for numbers. No exclamation marks. Never "RSVP," never raw enums, never bare "guests" as the collective noun (collides with **Guest Access** — see §11.2); the collective is **"confirmed"** or **"the room."**
+
+**Headline selection** (C = confirmed, R = returning as defined in §2):
+
+| Condition | Headline |
+|---|---|
+| C = 0 | Empty A (below) |
+| C > 0, workspace has no prior checked-in event | Empty B / "first room" (below) |
+| R = 0, club has history | "A room of new faces." |
+| 0 < R/C < 1/3 | "A new crowd, with a few familiar faces." |
+| 1/3 ≤ R/C < 2/3 | "A familiar room, meeting new faces." |
+| R/C ≥ 2/3 | "A room of familiar faces." |
+| Sold out (confirmed ≥ capacity) | Prefix replaces opener — see 6.3 |
+
+### 6.1 Healthy mixed crowd (e.g., C=32, R=18)
+
+- Headline: **"A familiar room, meeting new faces."**
+- Composition line: **"18 of 32 confirmed have been here before."** — exactly one sentence; the segment detail ("6 are regulars") was cut with the chips.
+- Faces to know: see §7 for the grammar; examples in §4.
+- Footer: **"Based on check-ins across your events · See the full list →"** (→ the event's guest list tab)
+
+### 6.2 All first-timers (club has history; this crowd is all new — C=24, R=0)
+
+- Headline: **"A room of new faces."**
+- Composition line: **"All 24 confirmed are here for the first time. Tonight is everyone's first impression."** (the first sentence is the composition fact; the second is voice, not a second metric)
+- Faces to know: section hidden. In its place, one line, `text-text-secondary`:
+  - If the Remember name is surfaced in UI (§11.1): **"No history yet — Remember starts tonight at the door."**
+  - If not: **"No history yet — tonight's check-ins start it."**
+- Footer: unchanged.
+
+### 6.3 Sold out (C=50 of 50, R=31, waitlist 12)
+
+- Headline composes fullness with the mix:
+  - Mostly returning: **"A full house — and a familiar one."**
+  - Mixed: **"A full house — regulars and new faces."**
+  - All new: **"A full house of new faces."**
+- Composition line: **"All 50 spots confirmed; 31 have been here before. 12 more on the waitlist."** (waitlist clause only when sold out with waitlist ≥ 1; waitlisted people are **not** in C, R, the composition line, or faces — they don't hold spots)
+- Everything else as 6.1.
+
+### 6.4 Empty states (two distinct cases)
+
+**A — No one confirmed yet** (any event, C=0):
+- Headline: **"No one confirmed yet."**
+- Deck: **"As confirmations come in, you'll see who's returning and who's brand new."**
+- Card collapses to eyebrow + these two lines. No faces, no footer link.
+
+**B — The first event ever** (zero history workspace-wide — *the "event #2 isn't a blank slate" promise, made at event #1*):
+- Headline: **"Your first room."**
+- Deck: **"Everyone tonight is a new face. Check them in at the door, and the history starts here — by event #2 you'll know exactly who came back."**
+- No faces section. Footer unchanged.
+
+### 6.5 Loading
+
+- Skeleton, not a spinner: eyebrow renders real; below it a headline-width shimmer bar, a composition-line bar, and 2–3 face-line bars. Fixed `min-height` matching the typical populated card — no layout shift on resolve.
+- Optional micro-caption under the eyebrow, `text-text-muted`: **"Reading the room…"**
+
+### 6.6 Error
+
+- The card degrades alone — it must never block or blank the rest of the Overview tab.
+- Eyebrow renders as normal. Body (Neue Haas, **not** the serif — errors are not editorial):
+  - **"Couldn't load who's coming."**
+  - **"The rest of this page is unaffected. Try again."** — "Try again" is a quiet text link that refetches, not a red button (an error retry should not be promoted to a primary CTA).
+- Implementation note (binding, from Absolute Rules): the catch that renders this **must log** the error with event id + workspace id context. No silent swallowing.
+
+## 7. Faces to know — how a notable surfaces
+
+Up to **3** lines (open decision §11.6). One line per person; each person appears once, with their **strongest** story. Selection priority, deterministic:
+
+1. **Back after a break** — `lapsed` and confirmed for this event, ordered by `eventsAttended` desc. The win-back is the best hosting story in the room.
+2. **Milestone** — this event would be their 5th, 10th, or 25th attendance.
+3. **Top spend** — highest `totalSpendCents` in the room (big spenders).
+4. **Most loyal** — highest `eventsAttended` (regulars), as backfill.
+
+**No-show risks never appear here** — nor anywhere else on this card since the chips were cut (2026-06-09). The spotlight is for hosting moments, not warnings; no-show names stay findable in the guest list.
+
+**Line grammar:** `{First name} {Last initial}. — {story}.` Maximum two facts, comma-separated, period end.
+
+Story fragments:
+- Ordinal: **"4th event"** (= prior attended + 1 — what tonight would make it)
+- Break length: **"back after 4 months"** (floor of days/30; 12+ months → **"back after over a year"**)
+- Spend: **"$1,240 lifetime"** (whole dollars, comma-grouped)
+- Loyalty: **"regular, 8 events"**
+- Recency phrasing alternative: **"first event since January"** (month name if within this calendar year; **"since March 2025"** otherwise)
+
+Examples:
+- **"Marcus K. — 4th event, back after 4 months."**
+- **"Sofia R. — regular, 8 events, $1,240 lifetime."**
+- **"Dana W. — first event since January."**
+
+## 8. Terminology audit (UI copy law)
+
+- "Access" / "Event Access" / "Comp Access" used canonically; **"RSVP" appears nowhere** on this card.
+- No raw enums ever (`WAITLISTED` → "on the waitlist"; segment keys → the display names in §6.1).
+- Collective noun is "confirmed" / "the room" — **not** "guests" (§11.2).
+- ⚠ **Adjacent drift, not this card's scope:** the existing stat card on this same tab is labeled **"Confirmed RSVPs"** (`EventOverviewTab.tsx:191`) — a standing violation of the no-RSVP law. Recommend renaming to "Confirmed" as a separate one-line fix.
+
+## 9. Accessibility
+
+- The card is a `region` with `aria-label="Who's coming — pre-event audience summary"`.
+- All meaning is carried in text; nothing rides on color alone.
+- All contrast via tokens (the token system is the AA guarantee); the italic serif headline stays ≥ ~20px.
+- Radix primitives for any tooltip, per house standard.
+
+## 10. Sponsor firewall — hard rules
+
+This card is **operator-authored-adjacent behavioral intelligence**: per-person spend, attendance counts, no-show history, lapse status. This is exactly the class of data the firewall exists to contain.
+
+1. Renders only inside `/operator/events/[id]` behind operator auth. Any API endpoint built to feed it is operator-authed and internal.
+2. **Never** enters the sponsor projection (`sponsor_audience_member`), the `lib/intelligence/sponsor-safe.ts` types, the Sponsor Intelligence dashboard, or any sponsor-visible aggregate.
+3. **Never** appears on external share surfaces — DAM share/gallery token pages, or any future public page.
+4. **Never** included in any export or AI-composed briefing that feeds sponsors. A sponsor must not be able to learn who spends what, who no-shows, or who lapsed.
+5. `tests/unit/sponsor-firewall.test.ts` remains the gate; the implementation must not widen any sponsor-safe type to carry these fields.
+
+## 11. Open decisions — Adam decides, do not infer
+
+1. **The "Remember" name in UI:** the eyebrow here is "WHO'S COMING" and the feature name stays internal. Should "Remember" be surfaced as product language? (§6.2 carries both copy variants.)
+2. **Collective noun:** bare "guests" collides with **Guest Access** (a specific access group). This spec uses "confirmed" / "the room." Sign off or supply the house word.
+3. **History window:** do the rows fed to `summarizeMemberHistory` for this card include the current event's own registration? Spec assumes **exclude** (returning = *prior* attendance). Affects every count on the card.
+4. ~~**No-show risk depth.**~~ **Resolved 2026-06-09:** the chip was cut with the whole segment layer; no-show risk does not appear on this card. Names stay behind a guest-list filter.
+5. **Plus-ones:** they have no individual history. Proposal: excluded from C/R math; when >0, append a deck footnote — **"Plus-ones add 6 more at the door."** Confirm.
+6. **Faces-to-know cap (3)** and whether lifetime **spend** belongs on those lines (visible to every operator role, including READ_ONLY).
+7. **Waitlist-only state** (C=0, waitlist >0): proposal — Empty A with one extra line: **"12 on the waitlist — no confirmed spots yet."**
+8. **Thresholds** (`DEFAULT_SEGMENT_THRESHOLDS`: 3 events / $500 / 2 no-shows / 120 days) ship as code constants. Workspace-configurable is a later decision; no settings UI in this spec.
+9. **"Confirmed RSVPs" label drift** (§8) — approve the rename as a separate fix.
+
+## 12. Out of scope
+
+- The post-event retro surface and the door "Nth event" badge (other Remember surfaces named in the engine header).
+- Any change to `lib/member-history.ts` semantics or thresholds.
+- The guest-list tab itself, segment filters there, and the CRM record page (see `OPERATOR-CRM-ROADMAP.md`).
+- Implementation: data fetching, caching, the API route. Engine is pure; the caller fetches RSVP rows joined to event start times.
