@@ -0,0 +1,207 @@
+# Members CRM — UX Flow + IA Spec (Draft)
+
+_Author: Draft (UX). Scope: flows, IA, interaction states, copy for the operator members CRM. No visual system (see form), no code (see prism). Locked terminology honored (Member, Guest, Comp Access, Event Access, never RSVP). Firewall honored: every artifact below is operator-internal and never sponsor-facing. Grounded in `app/operator/members/`, `OPERATOR-CRM-ROADMAP.md`, `INFLUENCE-MODEL.md`._
+
+---
+
+## 1. The job
+
+The operator runs the room. Four verbs, one surface:
+
+- **Capture** a person met anywhere, fast.
+- **Edit** what they know about that person fluidly, in place.
+- **Understand** how the room connects (referral spine, connectors).
+- **Curate** the roster: find, filter, segment, act.
+
+Done state for the whole CRM: the operator never feels they left a list to do a task. Capture, edit, and read happen without a context switch.
+
+---
+
+## 2. Information architecture (record + roster + connectors as one system)
+
+Today three surfaces are disconnected: roster (`/operator/members`), record (`/members/[id]`), connectors (`/members/connectors`), with field setup off in Settings and reporting destined for Intelligence.
+
+Proposed model: the **roster is the spine**. Everything is reachable from it or returns to it.
+
+```
+Members (roster)  ── primary operator nav item
+├── row click ........... Record (detail)
+├── header link ......... Connectors (influence lens)
+├── header button ....... Add Member (capture)
+└── header link ......... Field setup (deep-link to Settings → member-fields)
+
+Record (detail)
+├── breadcrumb .......... back to Members
+├── Sphere card ......... links up (referrer) + down (referred) to other Records
+│   └── "View all connectors" ... Connectors
+└── inline edit ......... stays on the Record
+
+Connectors (lens)
+└── row click ........... Record
+```
+
+### RESOLVED-IA-1 (founder, 2026-06-09) — Intelligence is the hub
+The reporting and member-intelligence layer coheres in **Intelligence** (`/operator/intelligence`), reaching back into Members. Field setup and the roster stay where they are; Intelligence is the place that aggregates and reports across them. The lens reporting dashboard builds here. Members remains the operational spine; Intelligence is the analysis hub.
+
+### OPEN-IA-2 — record sectioning at scale
+The record aside is a single growing stack (Notes, Assessment, Editable, Sphere, and reporting later). Decision: keep one column, or introduce record sections/tabs (Overview, Activity, Relationships, Fields) once it passes ~4 cards. Flag, do not assume.
+
+---
+
+## 3. Flow A — Capture (frictionless add)
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart TD
+    Start[Operator meets someone, opens Members] --> Add[Clicks Add Member]
+    Add --> Form[Capture panel opens, focus on first field]
+    Form --> Has{Has an email?}
+    Has -->|Yes| Fill[Enters name + email, optional company/phone/referrer]
+    Fill --> Save[Saves]
+    Save --> Toast[Toast: 'Jane Smith added' + Open record]
+    Toast --> Done[Row appears at top of roster]
+    Has -->|No, met in the wild| OpenQ[OPEN: Q-Capture path]
+    OpenQ -.->|name-only, synthetic email| SaveB[Saves as Guest]
+    OpenQ -.->|require email| Blocked[Cannot save without email]
+    SaveB --> Toast
+```
+
+### Decision: OPEN-CAPTURE-1 (Q-Capture)
+Context: operator meets someone with only a name, maybe an Instagram or phone. Email is the unique identity key (`@@unique([workspaceId, email])`).
+Branches, both viable, **founder decides**:
+- **Synthetic email** (recommended in roadmap): name-only saves; mint a hidden synthetic email; record shows name, not a fake address. Cost: two captures of the same no-email person can dup.
+- **Require email**: simplest identity model; cost: real capture friction at the top of funnel.
+Risk if wrong: either polluted identity data, or operators not capturing people at all.
+
+▲ FRICTION: today the create path requires first name, last name, AND email. "Met in the wild" is exactly the high-value, low-data moment, and it is currently blocked. This is the single biggest capture-flow gap. Resolution gated on OPEN-CAPTURE-1.
+
+### Copy (capture panel)
+- Trigger: `Add Member`
+- Title: `Add a member`
+- Fields: `Full name` (required), `Email`, `Company`, `Phone`, `Referred by`
+- Referred-by helper: `Who brought them in?`
+- Primary: `Add member` · busy: `Adding…`
+- Success toast: `{name} added` + action `Open record`
+- Duplicate error: `A member with this email already exists` + action `Open their record`
+
+---
+
+## 4. Flow B — Inline edit (roster cell + record)
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart TD
+    View[Operator scanning roster or reading a record] --> Click[Clicks an editable cell or field]
+    Click --> Edit[Cell becomes an input, value selected]
+    Edit --> Type[Types a value]
+    Type --> Commit{How do they leave?}
+    Commit -->|Enter or blur| Save[Saves, optimistic]
+    Commit -->|Escape| Cancel[Reverts, no write]
+    Save --> Ok{Server ok?}
+    Ok -->|Yes| Settled[Value sticks, provenance stamped]
+    Ok -->|No| RollbackErr[Reverts to prior value, red border, retry]
+```
+
+Editable in place:
+- **Roster cells:** Company today; extend to Role and Industry (firmographic, high-value-at-scale). Identity (name/email), computed (score/events/dates), and archetype (psychographic) stay read-only.
+- **Record:** firmographic fields, custom fields, referrer, notes (already inline).
+
+### RESOLVED-EDIT-1 (founder, 2026-06-09) — full customization
+The operator gets **full customization**: any editable field is inline-editable, and which columns the roster shows is operator-configurable (firmographic columns plus operator-defined custom fields). Still hard-excluded: identity (name/email), computed values (score/events/dates), and anything psychographic (archetype) per the firewall. So "full customization" means full control over the firmographic + custom-field surface, never over identity, computed, or firewalled data.
+
+▲ FRICTION: single-field saves with no batch. Acceptable for v1; flag if operators edit many fields per row.
+
+### States (every editable cell)
+- Default: value, or muted placeholder `Add company` when empty (STAFF+ only; READ_ONLY sees plain text or `—`).
+- Editing: input, autofocus, current value as draft.
+- Saving: input disabled.
+- Error: revert to prior value, red border, value stays editable to retry.
+- No-permission: plain text, no affordance.
+
+### Copy
+- Empty cell placeholder: `Add company` / `Add role` / `Add industry`
+- Save: Enter or click-away. Cancel: Esc. (No visible buttons in-cell.)
+- Error toast (optional): `Could not save. Try again.`
+
+---
+
+## 5. Flow C — Find and open
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart TD
+    Land[Operator opens Members] --> Scan[Sees roster, most recent first]
+    Scan --> Need{Looking for someone specific?}
+    Need -->|Yes| Search[Types name or email]
+    Need -->|Browse a segment| Facet[Picks a facet: Purple list / Attended / Blocked]
+    Search --> Narrow[Roster filters live, shows N of M]
+    Facet --> Narrow
+    Narrow --> Sort[Optional: sorts by Score, Events, Last seen, Joined]
+    Sort --> Open[Clicks a row]
+    Open --> Record[Record opens]
+    Narrow --> None{Any matches?}
+    None -->|No| Empty[Empty-match message + clear filters]
+```
+
+### States (roster)
+- Default: full roster, search + facets + sortable columns + bulk bar (on select).
+- Empty (no members at all): `No members yet` + `Add a member directly, or approve an application` link.
+- Empty-match (filter returns nothing): `No members match "{query}".` + implicit clear via deleting query / All facet.
+- Loading: server-rendered; the page arrives populated (no spinner needed). Sub-islands (notes, timeline, sphere) load on the record.
+- Error (roster fetch fails): `Could not load members.`
+
+### Copy
+- Search placeholder: `Search name or email…`
+- Facets: `All` · `Purple list` · `Attended` · `Blocked`
+- Count: `{visible} of {total}` (or `{total} members` when unfiltered)
+- Header links: `Connectors` · `Field setup` · button `Add Member`
+
+---
+
+## 6. Flow D — Relationships and influence
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart TD
+    Rec[Operator on a Record] --> Sphere[Reads Sphere of influence card]
+    Sphere --> SetRef{Referrer set?}
+    SetRef -->|No| Pick[Clicks Set referrer, searches a member, selects]
+    SetRef -->|Yes| Up[Clicks referrer to go up the chain]
+    Pick --> Stamp[Saved, appears on both records]
+    Sphere --> Down[Clicks a referred member to go down]
+    Sphere --> All[Clicks View all connectors]
+    All --> Rank[Connectors ranking]
+    Rank --> Rec
+```
+
+### States (Sphere card)
+- Default: `Referred by {name}` + `Referred {N}` list.
+- Empty: `Referred by` → `Not set` (+ `Set referrer` for STAFF+); `Referred` → `No referrals yet.`
+- Loading: `Loading…`
+- Error: `Could not load relationships.`
+- Picker empty-match: `No members match.`
+- Guarded write errors (surfaced inline): `A member cannot refer themselves.` · `That would create a circular referral.`
+
+### Copy
+- Labels: `Sphere of influence` · `Referred by` · `Referred`
+- Actions: `Set referrer` · `Change` · `Clear`
+- Cross-link: `View all connectors`
+- Connectors page: title `Connectors`, subtitle `Who built the room, ranked by members they referred who were approved.`, columns `Connector / Became members / Referred total`.
+
+---
+
+## 7. Consolidated open decisions
+
+| ID | Decision | Status | Resolution |
+|----|----------|--------|------------|
+| OPEN-CAPTURE-1 (Q-Capture) | No-email capture: synthetic email vs require email | **OPEN** | Recommend synthetic email, hidden from UI |
+| OPEN-EDIT-1 | Inline-edit / column scope | **RESOLVED** | Full customization: configurable columns + inline edit across firmographic + custom fields; identity/computed/psychographic excluded |
+| OPEN-IA-1 | Where member intelligence coheres | **RESOLVED** | Intelligence is the hub; Members is the operational spine |
+| OPEN-IA-2 | Record sectioning as cards grow | **OPEN** | Recommend tabs once >4 cards |
+
+## 8. Friction summary
+
+- ▲ Capture blocked without email (OPEN-CAPTURE-1). Highest-impact fix.
+- ▲ Inline edit is one column; extend to Role/Industry (OPEN-EDIT-1).
+- ▲ Field setup, values, and reporting live in three places (OPEN-IA-1).
+- ● No batch field edit; acceptable for v1.
+
+## 9. Key UX decisions made
+
+The roster is the spine and everything returns to it, so the operator never feels they left the list. Capture and edit are designed as in-place, low-ceremony actions (one panel, in-cell editing, Enter-to-save) rather than separate pages, which is what makes the surface feel like a working tool instead of a database. The one thing this spec refuses to decide is identity for no-email capture: it is a real product call (Q-Capture) with data-integrity consequences, so both branches are drawn and left for the founder. Everything here is operator-internal; none of it touches the sponsor projection.
