+# Overnight Platform Audit — NoBC OS
+
+**Date:** 2026-06-09
+
+## 1. Verdict
+
+NoBC OS is structurally sound for a single tenant, but launch is gated by a public-blob PII leak, several unauthenticated/unscoped object-access and webhook paths, untracked schema drift, and zero test coverage on the money and access-gate paths — all fixable before SaaS/multi-tenant rollout.
+
+## 2. Top 10 Findings (ranked across all domains)
+
+1. [CRITICAL] infra — Membership uploads land in a PUBLIC Vercel Blob bucket (PII-adjacent, no auth/expiry) — Move to private R2 under `applications/{workspaceId}/` behind a role-gated presign; treat existing objects as leaked.
+2. [CRITICAL] security — MCP write path has no role check — Add role gating to all MCP write tools.
+3. [CRITICAL] data — Tracked migrations diverge from live schema (out-of-band SQL never recorded) — Backfill matching migrations and `prisma migrate resolve --applied` against Neon, coordinated with Producer.
+4. [CRITICAL] data — `MemberEngagementEventType` enum: tracked migration has 8 values, schema/code use 18 — Add a tracked `ALTER TYPE ... ADD VALUE IF NOT EXISTS` migration and resolve it against prod.
+5. [CRITICAL] reliability — Inbound SMS lacks idempotency; Twilio retries double-text/double-charge — Add unique `providerSid` + `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`, ack 200 before triage.
+6. [CRITICAL] reliability — No queue-on-failure; Producer/Svix drops are silent — Cron-sweep failed-audit rows and alert.
+7. [CRITICAL] qa — Stripe webhook handler has zero test coverage — Add `tests/unit/stripe-webhook.test.ts` covering all four branches, bad-signature 400, and replay idempotency.
+8. [CRITICAL] qa — Event-access gate logic is pure, security-critical, and untested — Add `tests/unit/event-access.test.ts` covering the viewer × access-mode truth table and pay-before/pay-after gates.
+9. [WARNING] backend — Public event-hero presign is an unscoped object-access primitive (IDOR) — Resolve the caller-supplied key against the DB and 404 if no workspace owns it.
+10. [WARNING] security — Global `CHECKIN_SECRET` is cross-tenant — Move to a per-workspace secret with `workspaceId` scoping.
+
+## 3. Severity Totals
+
+```json
+{"CRITICAL":9,"WARNING":21,"INFO":14}
+```
+
+## 4. Per-Domain Reports
+
+- [Security](./today-security.md)
+- [Backend](./today-backend.md)
+- [Data](./today-data.md)
+- [Infra](./today-infra.md)
+- [Reliability](./today-reliability.md)
+- [QA](./today-qa.md)
+- [Frontend](./today-frontend.md)
+
+## 5. Recommended Morning Order
+
+1. **infra — Public membership-upload blob leak (CRITICAL).** This is a live data-exposure of PII-adjacent applicant files with no auth and no expiry — every minute it stays public widens the leak. Lock it down first and treat existing objects as compromised.
+2. **security — MCP write path role check (CRITICAL).** An unauthenticated write primitive is the highest-leverage abuse path in the platform; gating it is small, contained, and removes a whole class of mutation risk.
+3. **data — Migration/enum drift (the two data CRITICALs, done together).** They share one Producer-coordinated `migrate resolve` window, and the 8-vs-18 enum gap will hard-break `emitEvent` on any fresh build (CI shadow DB, new tenant, Producer migrate) — fix before the next deploy or new-tenant onboarding, not after.
