+# Platform Rating — CTO Health Assessment (2026-06-10)
+
+> Read-only assessment. Rated against the actual `main`-lineage code in
+> `/Users/adamsemien/nobc-os` (HEAD `chore/seed-gravity-ledger`) and the canonical
+> plan (`WEDGE-SLICE-PHASE-PLAN.md`, `STRATEGY-GTM-CUSTOMER-1.md`, thesis v2 §10).
+> "Hardened today" ≠ "shippable revenue" — the table distinguishes them.
+
+## Per-part rating
+
+| Part | Score | One-line justification |
+|---|---:|---|
+| Checkout / Payments (money path) | **5/10** | Authorize/capture is hardened (#70: Serializable tx, idempotencyKey, oversell race, dangling-PI cancel; #66 tested pricing). But **single-account only** — zero Stripe Connect (`application_fee`/`transfer_data`/`acct_` absent everywhere). Money can't reach an external creator → no customer 1 revenue. Solid foundation, half the product missing. |
+| Security / Tenancy / RBAC | **7/10** | Workspace scoping is real and consistent; 70/142 API routes `requireRole`-gated (reads intentionally open), check-in moved to signed tokens (#59), uploads private R2 (#50). Gap: `/api/mcp` **Bearer** write path still unauthed (design in flight). No RLS yet (defense-in-depth, gated on Producer convergence). |
+| CRM & Sphere-of-Influence (the moat) | **6/10** | The hard part is **built and intellectually honest**: `lib/member-connections.ts` derives gravity-in-dollars (captured-revenue attribution, "stuck" edges), and the doc bakes in the falsification result that KILLED the influence-score idea. This is the un-copyable wedge. But it's engine + seed + mid-build page — not yet a finished operator surface, and "Remember" Phase C (no-show/spend rollup/segments/retro) is unbuilt. |
+| AI surfaces (scoring / chat / builder / narration) | **4/10** | All present (archetype scoring, operator chat, event builder, SMS triage). But **archetype scoring is an unvalidated prior** — generated at apply-time, never backtested against attendance/spend/gravity. AI breadth without a proven outcome loop. The gravity engine is the one place AI is disciplined (narrates only what's proven). |
+| House Phone / SMS reliability | **5/10** | Architecture is sound (Railway inbound + nobc-os outbound, same DB). But **idempotency is in-flight, not landed** — `MessageSid` dedup + durable rate limiter gated on schema PR #73 (`twilioSid` column) which needs a manual `db execute` window. Until that lands, duplicate inbound = duplicate AI replies. Also not live (TWILIO_* unset). |
+| Reliability / Observability | **3/10** | **No APM** — no Sentry/OTel/Datadog anywhere. Error boundaries log to console only (#69 added a root boundary; #67/#70 fixed real race conditions). You're flying blind in production: a paid-checkout failure surfaces only if someone reads Vercel logs. Lowest score, highest asymmetry once money flows. |
+| Import & Data Unification | **2/10** | **Scoped only, zero code.** Patron identity is fragmented across Posh + Luma + ActiveCampaign; no source adapters, no identity resolution, no merge UI. Load-bearing for the whole influence thesis (fragmented identity → wrong gravity read) and entirely unbuilt. |
+| Demo-readiness ("holy shit" moment today) | **5/10** | You can demo: editorial event pages, ticketing, offline check-in, and the Gravity Ledger on **seed data** (real names/dollars after #75). That's a genuine "it knows who drives your room" moment. But it's seeded, not a real operator's unified data, and the money path / Remember surface aren't demo-complete. Compelling slice, not yet the closing demo. |
+
+## Overall
+
+**6.5 / 10 (platform vs. thesis) — flat vs. this morning (~6.5).**
+
+Today's merges were **consolidation, not advancement**: race-condition hardening
+(#67/#70), a global error boundary (#69), confirmation email+QR (#72), and the
+gravity engine + revenue attribution + seed (#71/#75). All real, all good
+hygiene — but every one strengthens what already worked or finishes the *engine*
+behind the moat. **None of it moved the two needles that gate revenue:** Stripe
+Connect (no money to a creator) and the finished Remember surface (the closing
+demo). The build got more durable; it did not get closer to customer 1's dollar.
+That's why the number holds rather than climbs. The thesis itself rates ~7.5
+(thesis v2) — the gap between 6.5 and 7.5 *is* the execution gap, and it's the
+right gap to be closing now.
+
+## Where to focus next (mapped to the phase plan)
+
+**#1 highest-leverage — Phase A: Stripe Connect (file the platform app TODAY).**
+*Reason: revenue + schedule.* It's the longest pole (external Stripe KYC/platform
+review is the critical path, not the code) and the literal precondition for
+customer-1 money. The application clock is wall-clock time you cannot compress —
+start it before writing a line. The code (`lib/stripe-connect.ts`, destination
+charges + `application_fee_amount`, additive `Workspace.stripeConnect*` fields) is
+3–4 weeks and well-scoped.
+
+**#2 — Phase C: finish "Remember" (the closing demo).** *Reason: moat → close.*
+No-show derivation, spend rollup, smart segments, event retro, returning-guest
+badge at the door. Runs **in parallel with A** (pure product, no Stripe
+dependency), additive-only on mature models, and it's the demo that makes a
+creator say "event #2 isn't a blank slate." This is what converts the pitch.
+
+**#3 — Phase D: minimum run-of-show.** *Reason: indispensability.* The narrowest
+back-of-house (ordered timeline + vendor contacts + day-of mobile view) that moves
+day-of ops off a spreadsheet and into NoBC — the "one tool instead of six" story.
+Hold the NOT-in-scope line hard (no SOWs/budgets/portals — that's Producer).
+
+**#4 (parallel, cheap) — land SMS idempotency + add basic observability.** *Reason:
+foundation.* Apply schema PR #73 in a coordinated window so `nobc-house-phone` PR
+#1 can ship (stops duplicate AI replies). And add Sentry (a half-day) before money
+flows — a 3/10 observability score is acceptable pre-revenue and indefensible the
+day a creator's checkout silently fails.
+
+### What would be FLUFF to build next
+- **An influence/centrality score** — already falsified (0/8 connectors caught,
+  0.85-correlated with attendance). Building a ranking on top of the engine is
+  re-adding the thing the data killed.
+- **Import/unification now** — load-bearing eventually, but it validates engine
+  logic against *imported* data that's mostly co-registration (no native
+  brought/proximity edges). Build the graph on-platform first; import the contact
+  list later (Phase B/D). Doing it now is effort against a graph that compounds
+  natively anyway.
+- **More AI surfaces / sponsor-facing intelligence polish** — thesis v2 demoted
+  intelligence to a supporting layer. More dashboards = "insight theater," not
+  indispensability.
+- **RLS / full Producer convergence** — correct long-term, but gated on the
+  convergence decision + Producer DB window; not on the path to customer 1.
+
+## Biggest risk to the thesis right now
+**You're choosing to fight Lu.ma/Posh on their home turf (free, network-effected,
+genuinely good front-of-house), and the only thing that makes a creator unable to
+go back — the production back-end + the captured-revenue memory — is exactly the
+part that is least finished.** Concretely: Stripe Connect is unbuilt, Remember is
+mid-build, run-of-show is one text field. If the next ~6 weeks ship more hardening
+and engine work instead of A+C+D, the product stays "a nicer Posh" — and "nicer"
+loses to "free + network." The mitigation is already written (the phase plan);
+the risk is purely whether execution stays on the revenue-and-moat path instead of
+drifting back into hardening and AI breadth, which is where the last day went.
