@@ -0,0 +1,70 @@
+# NoBC OS — Infra Audit (2026-06-09)
+
+**Verdict:** Mostly healthy — Prisma 7 driver-adapter DB wiring, R2 private DAM, cron auth, and the `serverExternalPackages` HEIC fix are all sound — but two real exposures need attention: membership-application file uploads are written to **public** Vercel Blob, and the `SVIX_*` env name in the example file does not match the code (the documented launch blocker can't be cleared by following the example).
+
+---
+
+### [CRITICAL] Membership application uploads land in a PUBLIC Vercel Blob bucket
+
+`app/api/apply/membership/upload/route.ts:23` writes applicant-supplied files with `put(key, buf, { access: 'public', contentType })` under a `applications/${Date.now()}-${random8}.ext` key (line 21). For a curated member club, `/apply` uploads are PII-adjacent (IDs, headshots, supporting docs). `access: 'public'` makes every uploaded object world-readable at a stable Vercel Blob URL with **no auth and no expiry** — and the key is only weakly unguessable (timestamp + 8 random base36 chars). The same pattern is used for event-hero uploads at `app/api/media/upload/route.ts:37`, which is lower-stakes but still public. This sits oddly next to the DAM, which (correctly) uses **private** R2 with 15-min signed GET URLs (`lib/dam/storage.ts:19,83`).
+
+**Evidence:** `app/api/apply/membership/upload/route.ts:21-23`; contrast `lib/dam/storage.ts:64-103` (private + presigned).
+
+**Fix:** Move membership uploads off public Blob. Either (a) write them to the existing private R2 bucket under an `applications/{workspaceId}/...` prefix and serve via a workspace-scoped, role-gated presign route (mirror `app/api/media/dam/asset/[id]/thumb/route.ts`), or (b) if staying on Vercel Blob, switch to a private/token-scoped access mode and proxy reads through an authenticated route. Treat the existing public objects as already-leaked and rotate/re-key any sensitive ones. Do not change `/apply` flow logic beyond the storage destination (Locked Decision: never break `/apply`).
+
+---
+
+### [WARNING] SVIX env var name in `.env.local.example` does not match the code — the documented launch blocker is mis-keyed
+
+CLAUDE.md "Remaining before full V1 launch" says to set `SVIX_API_KEY` in Vercel, and the code reads exactly that: `lib/svix.ts:6-7` gates on `process.env.SVIX_API_KEY`. But `.env.local.example:18` declares `SVIX_SECRET=` (wrong name). Anyone provisioning env from the example will set `SVIX_SECRET`, `getSvix()` will still return `null`, and outbound webhooks (V1 item #20) silently no-op with no error — the failure mode is invisible because `getSvix()` returns null rather than throwing.
+
+**Evidence:** `lib/svix.ts:6` (`SVIX_API_KEY`) vs `.env.local.example:18` (`SVIX_SECRET`).
+
+**Fix:** Rename the example line to `SVIX_API_KEY=` so it matches the code and the CLAUDE.md required list. Confirm the Vercel-side var is named `SVIX_API_KEY` before flipping webhooks live.
+
+---
+
+### [WARNING] Two parallel object stores (public Vercel Blob + private R2) — cost + operational duplication
+
+The app runs two storage backends at once: Vercel Blob (`@vercel/blob`, `put(... access:'public')`) for event-hero and membership uploads, and Cloudflare R2 (private, signed) for the DAM (`lib/dam/storage.ts`, `lib/r2-presign.ts`). Vercel Blob is billed separately from R2 (storage + egress on Vercel's plan, which is materially pricier per-GB than R2's zero-egress model), and the codebase already maintains a complete R2 client with a private-bucket convention. Maintaining both means two cost lines, two access models (one public, one private), and two mental models for "where do images live."
+
+**Evidence:** `app/api/media/upload/route.ts:3,37` and `app/api/apply/membership/upload/route.ts:2,23` (Blob) vs `lib/dam/storage.ts` + `lib/r2-presign.ts` (R2). `.env.local` carries both `BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN` and `R2_*`.
+
+**Fix:** Consolidate event-hero and membership uploads onto the existing R2 bucket (reuse `uploadObject` / `presignGet`), then drop the `@vercel/blob` dependency and `BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN`. This also resolves the CRITICAL above for free. Lower priority than the public-access fix but removes a recurring cost line.
+
+---
+
+### [WARNING] DAM thumbnail route sets no `Cache-Control` — every grid scroll re-mints a signed URL and re-hits R2
+
+`app/api/media/dam/asset/[id]/thumb/route.ts:28` 302-redirects to a freshly presigned R2 URL on every request, with no `Cache-Control` header on the redirect and none set on the R2 object (no `ResponseCacheControl` in `lib/dam/storage.ts:presignGet`). The grid `<img>` uses `loading="lazy"` (`MediaTile.tsx:49`) but the browser still re-fetches `/api/media/dam/asset/{id}/thumb` (and thus a new presign + R2 Class B GET) on each scroll-in / remount, because the redirect target changes every time and is uncacheable. For a media library with hundreds of thumbnails this is avoidable R2 operation cost and Vercel function invocations.
+
+**Evidence:** `app/api/media/dam/asset/[id]/thumb/route.ts:26-28` (no cache header); `lib/dam/storage.ts:83-103` (presign sets no `ResponseCacheControl`).
+
+**Fix:** Add `Cache-Control: private, max-age=600` (well under the 15-min TTL) to the 302 response so the browser caches the redirect for a single render session, and/or set `ResponseCacheControl` on the presigned GET. Keep max-age strictly below `DISPLAY_URL_TTL` so a cached URL never outlives its signature.
+
+---
+
+### [INFO] Member Pass renders QR via an external third-party service instead of the in-repo `qrcode` minting path
+
+`app/m/pass/page.tsx:30` builds the member's pass QR from `https://api.qrserver.com/v1/create-qr-code/?...&data=<memberQrCode>`. The repo already depends on `qrcode` and uses it server-side everywhere else (`app/m/events/[slug]/confirmed/page.tsx`, `lib/agent/tools/rsvps/comp-ticket.ts`, etc.), and CLAUDE.md notes `lib/member-qr.ts` is the single mint path. Routing the pass QR through `api.qrserver.com` (a) sends the member's QR token to an unmanaged third party, (b) adds an external availability dependency on the door-check-in path, and (c) is inconsistent with the rest of the codebase.
+
+**Evidence:** `app/m/pass/page.tsx:29-31` vs in-repo `qrcode` usage (`grep QRCode app`).
+
+**Fix:** Generate the QR as a data URL server-side with the existing `qrcode` dep (as `confirmed/page.tsx` already does) and render that, dropping the `api.qrserver.com` call. Note: the `import Image from 'next/image'` at line 5 is dead — the file renders a plain `<img>` — so it can be removed too.
+
+---
+
+### [INFO] `next/image` is effectively unused — no `remotePatterns` needed, and none is configured (correct)
+
+The audit brief flags `next/image` remote-host config. Confirmed there is no exposure here: the only `next/image` import (`app/m/pass/page.tsx:5`) is dead (the component uses `<img>`), DAM tiles use a same-origin `<img src="/api/media/dam/asset/.../thumb">` proxy (`MediaTile.tsx:46-47`), and R2/Blob images are served same-origin or via redirect. So `next.config.ts` having **no** `images.remotePatterns` is correct — adding remote hosts now would be unnecessary attack surface. Leave it as-is. (If anything ever switches to `<Image>` against a signed R2/Blob URL, that's when `remotePatterns` would be required.)
+
+---
+
+### What's healthy
+
+- **DB wiring (Prisma 7 driver adapter):** `schema.prisma` `datasource db` intentionally omits `url`/`directUrl` because the Neon driver adapter supplies the connection at runtime (`lib/db.ts:2,7` → `PrismaNeon({ connectionString: DATABASE_URL })`), with `prisma.config.ts` loading `.env.local` for CLI ops. This is the correct Prisma 7 pattern, not a missing-url bug. `DIRECT_URL` is correctly reserved for the manual `prisma db execute` migration workflow (referenced in `prisma/sql/*.sql` headers), consistent with the "never `db push`" Absolute Rule.
+- **HEIC serverless bundling:** `next.config.ts:10` externalizes `heic-convert` + `libheif-js` so the `.wasm` is traced into the Vercel bundle, and `lib/dam/heic.ts:26` dynamically imports it so the WASM only loads when a HEIC actually arrives. `app/api/media/dam/upload/route.ts:18-19` correctly pins `runtime = 'nodejs'` + `maxDuration = 60` for the Sharp/WASM decode. Well-reasoned.
+- **R2 DAM privacy:** private bucket, workspace-scoped keys (`dam/{workspaceId}/...`), short-lived signed GETs (15 min display / 24 hr download), graceful null when unconfigured. `/thumb` route is role-gated (`requireRole(READ_ONLY)`) and workspace-scoped before presigning.
+- **Cron auth:** `vercel.json` declares one cron; `app/api/cron/event-reminders/route.ts` authenticates on `CRON_SECRET` via both `authorization: Bearer` and `x-vercel-cron-secret`, rejecting when unset/mismatched.
+- **Sponsor firewall intact (not modified):** `lib/intelligence/sponsor-safe.ts` and the gate test `tests/unit/sponsor-firewall.test.ts` are present and untouched by this read-only audit.
+- **Secrets hygiene:** `.gitignore` covers `.env*`; no secret values were read or emitted during this audit (env keys inspected with values redacted).
